    explanationC: "Omalizumab does NOT destroy B-cells — it only captures free IgE. B-cells continue to produce IgE, which is neutralized in circulation. This is why ongoing treatment is needed.",
    explanationD: "Correct. Anti-IgE (Cε3 domain binding) prevents FcεRI engagement → no mast cell degranulation → prevents both early and late phase allergic responses. FcεRI downregulation provides long-term benefit.",
